verbose_text: Fresh samples of peat soils, collected about every 3 months for 20 months and incubated at 22 +/- 2degreesC regardless of the in situ temperature, exhibited potential rates of methane (CH 4) production of 0.02-0.2 mmol L -1 day -1 [380-3800 nmol g -1 (dry) day -1).
